{% set title_tag = "EightShapes > Discovery > Crafting Discovery Workshop" %}
{% set body_classes = "escom-page-type--marketing" %}
{% extends 'templates/base.njk' %}
{% block body %}

    {# Breadcrumb #}

    {{ esds.breadcrumb(section_href="/design-discovery.html", section="Design Discovery") }}

    {# Title #}

    {{ escom.title_row(
        class="esds-row--very-tall-inset",
        logo=false, 
        heading="Discovery Training Workshop",
        decks=[
            "Looking to get your team up-to-speed on the discovery process? In this training workshop, we’ll give them the tools they need to plan their own discovery phases."
        ]) }}

    {# Why #}

    {% call esds.row(background="white", class="esds-row--tall-inset") %}
        <div class="escom-long-form-text">
            <h2>Why a Workshop?</h2>
            <p class="escom-long-form-text__lead">
                Discovery is messy, chaotic, and poorly defined. Is it just research? Or something more? Do all your teams do discovery in the same way? Should they?
            </p>
            <p>In this workshop we’ll take a step back from the day-to-day, looking across discovery efforts to understand what they have in common. We’ll look at what makes them more than research, and how to make them practical for any effort. We’ll establish a vocabulary for talking about how to do discovery. With this foundation, we’ll ask teams to map their process so everyone has a clear picture of what everyone else is doing.</p>
        </div>
    {% endcall %}

    {# What You Get #}

    {% call esds.row(background="light", class="esds-row--tall-inset") %}
        <div class="escom-long-form-text">
            <h2>What You Get</h2>
            <p class="escom-long-form-text__lead">
                With EightShapes’ experience and enthusiasm, you’ll inspire your teams and energine your discovery efforts. Your team will get:
            </p>
            <div class="escom-long-form-text--two-column-at-768">
                <ul>
                    <li>Framework for planning their discovery efforts</li>
                    <li>Common language for discussing discovery with their stakeholders</li>
                    <li>Practice creating problem statements</li>
                </ul>
                <ul>
                    <li>Customizable discovery project plan </li>
                    <li>Sample discovery documentation</li>
                    <li>Essential discovery habits and behaviors</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
        </div>
    {% endcall %}

    {# What We Cover #}

    {% call esds.row(background="white", class="esds-row--tall-inset") %}
        <div class="escom-long-form-text">
            <h2>What We Cover</h2>
            <p class="escom-long-form-text__lead">
                The first half of the workshop covers theory, the building blocks of what discovery is and why it’s important. The second half goes into the practicalities of determining a schedule and outputs for discovery.
            </p>
            <p class="escom-long-form-text__lead">
                Both halves include exercises throughout to reinforce the concepts and provide some experience with discovery techniques. We can customize the exercises to align with current projects or challenges facing your team.
            </p>
        </div>

